20was%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20developed%20a%20personal%20philosophy.%20It%20basically%20amounted%20to%3A%20Earn%20more%2C%20spend%20less%2C%20invest%20the%20rest.%20It%20was%20a%20nice%20little%20mantra.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ffinancial-independence-retire-early%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELean%20FIRE%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20is%20when%20you%20live%20like%20a%20monk%20or%20like%20a%20grad%20student.%20Basically%2C%20you%20don't%20necessarily%20have%20to%20be%20broke%20or%20be%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-employees-use-frupidity-mix-frugality-stupidy-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrupid%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20when%20you%20make%20stupid%20decisions%20just%20to%20save%20money%20and%20it%20backfires.%20It's%20just%20about%20living%20within%20your%20means%20and%20not%20focusing%20on%20consumerism%20and%20capitalism%2C%20but%20rather%20enjoying%20the%20little%20things%20in%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20several%20years%20just%20trying%20to%20keep%20my%20head%20above%20the%20water%2C%20financially%20speaking%2C%20working%20manual%20jobs%20at%20Amazon%20warehouses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20book%20by%20Tim%20Ferriss%20called%20%26quot%3BThe%204-Hour%20Workweek.%26quot%3B%20When%20it%20came%20out%20in%202007%2C%20it%20was%20really%20revolutionary.%20He%20wrote%20about%20a%20bunch%20of%20things%2C%20but%20one%20of%20my%20favorite%20concepts%20was%20geographic%20arbitrage.%20Basically%2C%20you%20can%20enjoy%20the%20same%20standard%20of%20living%2C%20or%20even%20better%2C%20someplace%20way%20cheaper%20and%20way%20nicer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20long-term%20plan%20was%20to%20leverage%20my%20Amazon%20seniority%20and%20my%20skill%20set%20into%20getting%20transferred%20to%20one%20of%20our%20offices%20abroad.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20write%20a%20five-year%20plan.%20It%20said%20that%20within%20five%20years%20I%20was%20going%20to%20move%20to%20a%20slightly%20more%20civilized%20country%20with%20better%20healthcare%20and%20a%20cheaper%20standard%20of%20living.%20And%20that%20I%20will%20be%20able%20to%20squirrel%20away%20enough%20money%20to%20set%20off%20on%20the%20most%20basic%20Lean%20FIRE%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20updated%20the%20plan%20every%20three%20months%20religiously%20and%20managed%20to%20accomplish%20the%20plan%20three%20months%20ahead%20of%20schedule%2C%20in%20May%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20tried%20to%20save%20almost%20half%20of%20my%20paycheck%20and%20sometimes%20contributed%2090%25%20to%20my%20401(k)%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20living%20in%20Seattle%2C%20I%20did%20my%20best%20to%20save%20a%20big%20chunk%20of%20my%20paycheck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20using%20almost%20every%20trick%20in%20the%20book.%20I%20would%20cook%20at%20home%2C%20I%20would%20use%20my%20little%20slow%20cooker%20to%20make%20some%20chicken%2C%20beans%2C%20and%20garlic%2C%20and%20eat%20it%20at%20work.%20I%20think%20it%20amounted%20to%20about%20%242%20a%20portion%2C%20while%20all%20of%20my%20coworkers%20were%20going%20out%20to%20those%20food%20trucks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20there's%20this%20great%20huge%20light%20show%20in%20the%20sky%20twice%20a%20day%20every%20single%20day%20%E2%80%94%20the%20sunrise%20and%20sunset%2C%20but%20how%20many%20people%20actually%20stop%20to%20take%20a%20look%3F%20If%20they%20could%20charge%20you%20money%20for%20it%2C%20they%20would.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20to%20fun%20local%20events%20with%20my%20friends%2C%20different%20presentations%20and%20art%20gallery%20openings%20%E2%80%94%20and%20work%20presentations%20%E2%80%94%20to%20score%20free%20cider%20and%20snacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20almost%20never%20bought%20new%20books%20or%20entertainment.%20I%20would%20just%20use%20a%20local%20library%2C%20which%20is%20a%20severely%20underappreciated%20resource.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20posing%20on%20snow%20in%20front%20of%20a%20National%20Park%20sign.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e1efc390413ab8e1d834da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELukin%20hiking%20in%20California.%3Cp%3EGrigory%20Lukin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20maintain%20a%20%243%2C000%20emergency%20fund%20and%20put%20everything%20else%20that%20was%20left%20over%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20month%20into%20my%20taxable%20investment%20account.%20The%20percentage%20varied%2C%20but%20I%20believe%20every%20single%20month%2C%20I%20would%20save%20between%2025%25%20and%2045%25%20of%20my%20paycheck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20I%20would%20squirrel%20away%20enough%20money%20for%20a%20few%20months%20so%20that%20I%20could%20switch%20my%20401(k)%20contribution%20from%2010%25%20to%2090%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20paycheck%20would%20look%20absolutely%20hilarious.%20It%20would%20basically%20say%20%24100%20after%20all%20the%20fees%20and%20taxes.%20As%20long%20as%20you%20remember%20to%20flip%20it%20back%20to%20a%2010%25%20contribution%2C%20it%20was%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20was%20able%20to%20supplement%20my%20income%20with%20relocation%20bonuses%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20made%20even%20close%20to%20%24100%2C000%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20salary%20was%20about%20%2459%2C000%2C%20and%20then%20there%20would%20be%20a%20variable%20number%20of%20stock%20options.%20I%20was%20a%20low-level%20Amazonian.%20So%20if%20I%20could%20do%20it%2C%20anyone%20could%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20started%20at%20Amazon%20in%20November%202009%20as%20a%20temporary%20seasonal%20worker%2C%20packing%20boxes%20in%20Reno.%20I%20got%20a%20permanent%20position%20in%20May%202010%20and%20transferred%20to%20Las%20Vegas%20in%20September%202011.%20In%20August%202012%2C%20I%20became%20a%20quality%20analyst%20in%20the%20ICQA%20%3C%2Fspan%3E(inventory%20control%2C%20quality%20assurance)%20%3Cspan%3Edepartment.%20I%20then%20transferred%20and%20helped%20launch%20Amazon's%20fulfillment%20centers%20in%20Fort%20Worth%20and%20Tampa%2C%20in%20the%20same%20quality%20analyst%20role.%20I%20transferred%20to%20Seattle%20and%20leveled%20up%20to%20the%20lowest%20corporate%20tier%20in%20August%202015%3A%20my%20job%20title%20became%20business%20analyst%20on%20PPT%20(Production%20Planning%20Team).%20In%20May%202017%2C%20I%20transferred%20to%20FBA%20(Fulfillment%20by%20Amazon)%20and%20worked%20there%20as%20an%20investigation%20specialist.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Amazon%2C%20when%20you%20work%20as%20a%20warehouse%20employee%2C%20every%20time%20they%20open%20a%20new%20warehouse%20somewhere%20else%20in%20the%20country%2C%20they%20give%20you%20a%20%2410%2C000%20cash%20bonus%20if%20you%20transfer%20there.%20They%20take%20away%20one-third%20for%20taxes%20right%20away%2C%20so%20basically%2C%20they%20give%20you%20%246%2C700%20cash%20in%20your%20bank%20account.%20You%20have%20to%20figure%20out%20your%20own%20move%20and%20just%20show%20up%20in%20this%20warehouse.%20That's%20how%20I%20moved%20from%20Reno%20to%20Las%20Vegas%20to%20Fort%20Worth%20to%20Tampa%2C%20and%20then%20to%20Seattle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20course%20of%20three%20years%2C%20I%20tried%20to%20transfer%20to%20the%20UK%20%E2%80%94%20before%20Brexit%20%E2%80%94%20Poland%2C%20Canada%2C%20Australia%2C%20and%20then%20Canada%20again.%20And%20it%20finally%20worked.%20I%20got%20a%20transfer%20from%20Seattle%20to%20Toronto%20in%20March%202019%2C%20where%20I%20became%20a%20financial%20analyst%20attached%20to%20a%20nearby%20fulfillment%20center.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20an%20awesome%20road%20trip%20%E2%80%94%20I%20just%20shoved%20everything%20into%20my%20little%20Kia%20Rio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20about%20two%20years%20on%20a%20work%20permit%20until%20I%20got%20my%20permanent%20resident%20status.%20By%20then%2C%20it%20was%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20quit%20Amazon%20in%20May%202021.%20I%20spent%2011-and-a-half%20years%20working%20for%20Amazon%20altogether.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20I%20sold%20all%20of%20my%20Amazon%20stock%2C%20which%20I%20had%20been%20stockpiling%20for%20years.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20it%20was%20an%20all-time%20high%20and%20the%20only%20stock%20that%20was%20still%20going%20up.%20I%20used%20that%20money%20to%20invest%20in%20companies%20that%20were%20basically%20on%20sale%2C%2050%25%20or%2060%25%20off%20your%20shopping%20malls%2C%20cruise%20ships%2C%20airlines%2C%20and%20a%20couple%20of%20other%20companies%20like%20that.%20Within%20the%20years%20that%20followed%2C%20I%20believe%20my%20total%20return%20was%20293%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20finally%20stopped%20working%20after%20moving%20to%20Canada%2C%20and%20it's%20way%20easier%20to%20save%20here%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20highly%20recommend%20geographic%20arbitrage%2C%20or%20moving%20to%20other%20countries%2C%20to%20absolutely%20everybody%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I'm%20biased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoving%20to%20another%20country%20was%20the%20foundation%20of%20my%20big%20plan.%20When%20I%20moved%20to%20Toronto%2C%20I%20took%20a%2048%25%20pay%20cut%20in%20my%20total%20compensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20only%20in%20Toronto%20because%20it%20was%20part%20of%20the%20plan%20to%20move%20to%20Canada.%20Once%20I%20didn't%20have%20to%20stay%20there%20because%20of%20Amazon%2C%20I%20finally%20had%20a%20choice%20to%20make%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20my%20adult%20life%3A%20I%20could%20move%20to%20any%20city%20I%20wanted%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20taking%20a%20selfie.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e1ef3f90413ab8e1d83465%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELurkin%20in%20Quebec%20City.%3Cp%3EGrigory%20Lukin%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20personal%20opinion%2C%20aside%20from%20some%20similarities%2C%20Canada%20is%20suspiciously%20similar%20to%20the%20United%20States.%20There%20are%20some%20differences.%20Instead%20of%20guns%2C%20they%20have%20maple%20syrup%3B%20instead%20of%20miles%2C%20you%20have%20kilometers.%20But%20I%20didn't%20feel%20foreign%20enough.%20Quebec%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20was%20this%20mysterious%20province%20with%20its%20own%20alternate%20history.%20I%20visited%20Quebec%20City%20to%20do%20some%20apartment%20hunting%20and%20just%20absolutely%20fell%20in%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20provinces%20in%20Canada%20that%20have%20rent%20control%2C%20like%20British%20Columbia%20and%20Quebec%2C%20but%20Quebec%20enforces%20it%20a%20lot%20better%20than%20all%20the%20others.%20The%20cheapest%20cities%20to%20live%20in%20are%20in%20Quebec.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20lease%20in%20Toronto%20ended%20in%20September%202021%2C%20I%20packed%20everything%20up%20into%20a%20U-Haul%20trailer%2C%20sold%20my%20car%2C%20and%20moved%20to%20Quebec%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESaving%20here%20is%20infinitely%20easier.%20When%20I%20moved%2C%20my%20rent%20was%20all-inclusive%20for%20a%20nice%20large%20apartment%20on%20the%20second%20floor%20of%20a%20brick%20building%20next%20to%20the%20tourist%20sector.%20The%20rent%20was%20about%20670%20Canadian%20(or%20%24493)%2C%20and%20that's%20inclusive%20of%20electricity%2C%20fast%20internet%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20the%20whole%20thing.%20Now%20it's%20going%20up%20a%20little%20bit%20to%20730%20Canadian%20plus%2040%20Canadian%20for%20electricity%20(%24567).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can't%20get%20anything%20in%20the%20States%20for%20that%20kind%20of%20money%20in%20terms%20of%20your%20own%20apartment%20in%20a%20brick%2C%20soundproof%2C%20building%20%E2%80%94%20just%20beautiful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20entire%20past%20year%20in%202023%2C%20I%20think%20I've%20only%20bought%20a%20few%20new%20material%20things%3A%20a%20couple%20of%20books%2C%20a%20new%20pair%20of%20jeans%2C%20and%20some%20socks%2C%20and%20that%20was%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20gain%20pleasure%20from%20simple%20things%2C%20like%20learning%20to%20cook%20with%20my%20Instant%20Pot%20is%20amazing.%20I%20enjoy%20a%20very%20nice%20healthy%20and%20balanced%20diet.%20Going%20out%20and%20having%20fun%20and%20all%20of%20that%20definitely%20fits%20into%20a%20%24%201%2C000-a-month%20budget%2C%20give%20or%20take.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20recommend%20everyone%20at%20least%20consider%20geographic%20arbitrage%2C%20if%20not%20to%20another%20country%2C%20then%20maybe%20another%20city%20or%20another%20state.%20I%20know%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20rooted%20to%20where%20they%20are%20through%20their%20community%2C%20family%2C%20friends.%20But%20it's%20kind%20of%20like%20%26quot%3BLord%20of%20the%20Rings%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20little%20hobbits%20who%20are%20reluctant%20to%20leave%20their%20village%20until%20they%20absolutely%20have%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20you%20move%20is%20the%20most%20difficult%2C%20and%20then%20it%20just%20gets%20easier%20and%20easier%20every%20single%20time.%20Being%20this%20modern-day%2C%20nomadic%20vagabond%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20fun%20if%20you%20let%20it%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-worker-financial-independence-retire-early-fire-in-canada-cheaper-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709678114000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e79a0e90413ab8e1d98a66%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-worker-financial-independence-retire-early-fire-in-canada-cheaper-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Grigory%20Lukin%20saved%20most%20of%20his%20Amazon%20salary%20and%20relocation%20bonuses%20so%20he%20could%20retire%20early.%20He%20chose%20Canada%2C%20where%20it's%20cheaper%20to%20live%20well.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpandy%40insider.com%20(Jordan%20Pandy)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A174%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A