2%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Euro-American%20Artistic%20Ideas%20Are%20Used%20to%20Celebrate%20Africanness%20in%20the%20DR%20Congo%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F05200651%2FKinshasa.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhat%20kind%20of%20art%20is%20left%20behind%20by%20totalitarian%20regimes%3F%20A%20new%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmuse.jhu.edu%2Fbook%2F113312%5C%22%3Efree-to-read%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.umich.edu%2FBooks%2FC%2FCongo-Style2%5C%22%3Ebook%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0called%20%3C%2Fem%3ECongo%20Style%3A%20From%20Belgian%20Art%20Nouveau%20to%20African%20Independence%3Cem%3E%20explores%20the%20visual%20culture%2C%20architecture%20and%20heritage%20sites%20of%20the%20country%20today%20known%20as%20the%20Democratic%20Republic%20of%20Congo%20(DRC).%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIt%20does%20so%20by%20exploring%20two%20now-notorious%20regimes%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fbiography%2FLeopold-II-king-of-Belgium%5C%22%3EKing%20Leopold%20II%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99s%20rule%20(1885-1908)%20of%20Belgium%E2%80%99s%20Congo%20colony%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fbiography%2FMobutu-Sese-Seko%5C%22%3EMobutu%20Sese%20Seko%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99s%20totalitarian%20Zaire%2C%20established%20when%20he%20seized%20power%20in%20a%20military%20coup%20in%201965%20after%20five%20years%20of%20political%20upheaval.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20asked%20artist%20and%20visual%20culture%20scholar%20Ruth%20Sacks%20five%20questions%20about%20her%20book.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20did%20you%20set%20out%20to%20achieve%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYears%20ago%2C%20while%20I%20was%20in%20Belgium%20on%20an%20art%20residency%2C%20I%20became%20interested%20in%20the%20early%20modernist%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fart%2FArt-Nouveau%5C%22%3Eart%20nouveau%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0movement%20(1890-1914).%20In%20architecture%20and%20art%2C%20this%20period%20is%20part%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fart%2FModernism-art%5C%22%3E20th%20century%20modernism%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20known%20for%20a%20minimal%2C%20clean%20aesthetic%20that%E2%80%99s%20influenced%20by%20new%20technologies%20and%20the%20advent%20of%20machines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArt%20nouveau%20is%20distinctive%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20highly%20decorative%2C%20while%20still%20using%20the%20new%20building%20materials%20of%20iron%20and%20glass.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20290px)%2085vw%2C%20290px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F05194535%2FCongo-Style-200x300.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22290%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F05194535%2FCongo-Style-200x300.jpg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F05194535%2FCongo-Style-683x1024.jpg%20683w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F05194535%2FCongo-Style.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700278%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22435%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERuth%20Sacks%20%3Cem%3ECongo%20Style%3C%2Fem%3E%20University%20of%20Michigan%20Press%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20interested%20me%20was%20the%20colonial%20nature%20of%20art%20nouveau.%20Art%20nouveau%20came%20with%20a%20very%20strong%20sense%20of%20defining%20newly%20formed%20(or%20unified)%20nation%20states%20in%20western%20Europe.%20It%20was%20the%20style%20used%20at%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Ftopic%2Fworlds-fair%5C%22%3Eworld%20fairs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20were%20grand%20exhibitions%20showing%20off%20Western%20countries%E2%80%99%20scientific%20and%20cultural%20achievements%2C%20including%20the%20acquisition%20of%20colonies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20colonial%20pavilion%20in%20the%20art%20nouveau%20style%20at%20the%201897%20Brussels%20world%20fair%20in%20Belgium%20helped%20establish%20one%20of%20the%20names%20for%20Belgian%20art%20nouveau%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theparliamentmagazine.eu%2Fnews%2Farticle%2Fart-nouveau-year-brussels%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CStyle%20Congo%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20style%20is%20distinctive%20for%20its%20curling%2C%20plant-like%20shapes%20and%20is%20a%20major%20tourist%20feature%20today.%20The%20years%20in%20which%20it%20was%20implanted%20in%20Brussels%20(about%201890-1905)%20directly%20coincided%20with%20the%20brutal%20Congo%20regime%20of%20Belgium%E2%80%99s%20King%20Leopold%20II.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETravelling%20to%20the%20DRC%2C%20I%20located%20actual%20art%20nouveau%20buildings%20from%20the%20early%20colonial%20period.%20But%20it%20was%20the%20state%20sites%20of%20the%20early%20Mobutu%20Sese%20Seko%20regime%20(1965%20to%201975)%20that%20captured%20my%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20art%20nouveau%2C%20they%20are%20steeped%20in%20a%20sense%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foxfordre.com%2Fpolitics%2Fdisplay%2F10.1093%2Facrefore%2F9780190228637.001.0001%2Facrefore-9780190228637-e-2039%5C%22%3Enationalism%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20aimed%20at%20impressing.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20Limete%20Tower%20(in%20use%20from%201974)%20on%20Boulevard%20Lumumba%20is%20a%20massive%20monument%20intended%20to%20be%20a%20museum%20celebrating%20national%20culture.%20A%20tower%20made%20up%20of%20a%20huge%20raw%20cement%20tube%20is%20topped%20by%20an%20organic%20floret%20shaped%20crown%2C%20with%20a%20curving%20walkway%20leading%20off%20from%20its%20rounded%20lower%20sections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20experience%20of%20the%20capital%20city%2C%20Kinshasa%2C%20made%20me%20rethink%20what%20cities%20were%20and%20could%20be.%20Buildings%20like%20Limete%20Tower%20that%20were%20designed%20for%20very%20different%20infrastructures%20(far%20more%20ordered%2C%20European%20and%20US%20systems)%20have%20weathered%20in%20fascinating%20ways%20that%20are%20often%20related%20to%20extremely%20violent%20historic%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20present%20a%20conventional%20study%20that%20only%20analyses%20the%20design%20of%20the%20architecture%20and%20its%20functionality.%20The%20book%20attempts%20to%20read%20sites%20like%20this%20within%20the%20particularities%20of%20their%20city%2C%20its%20streets%2C%20plants%20and%20histories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20did%20you%20conclude%20about%20the%20Leopold%20period%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20199px)%2085vw%2C%20199px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F05195305%2FArt-nouveau-style-jpg-199x300.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22199%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F05195305%2FArt-nouveau-style-jpg-199x300.jpg%20199w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F05195305%2FArt-nouveau-style-jpg-680x1024.jpg%20680w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F05195305%2FArt-nouveau-style-jpg.jpg%20797w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700280%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EArt%20nouveau%20style.%20Artwork%3A%20Ruth%20Sacks%2FThe%20Conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Leopold%20II%E2%80%99s%20time%2C%20the%20king%20himself%20was%20cast%20as%20the%20villain%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cred%20rubber%20regime%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20Congo.%20The%20Belgian%20colonial%20regime%20under%20Leopold%20II%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amdigital.co.uk%2Finsights%2Fnews%2Fred-rubber-atrocities-in-the-congo-free-state-in-confidential-print-africa%5C%22%3Ecommitted%20atrocities%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0connected%20to%20the%20rubber%20industry.%20(The%201897%20Congo%20Pavilion%20was%20a%20pavilion%20within%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bie-paris.org%2Fsite%2Fen%2F1897-brussels%5C%22%3EBrussels%20World%E2%80%99s%20Fair%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0dedicated%20to%20displaying%20how%20the%20Congo%20provided%20a%20lucrative%20and%20exotic%20resource%20to%20Belgium.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMovements%20like%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.congoreformassociation.org%2Fcra-history%5C%22%3ECongo%20Reform%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0(mainly%20US%20and%20British)%20protested%20against%20horrific%20conditions%2C%20including%20torture%20and%20mutilation%2C%20that%20left%20at%20least%20a%20million%20Congolese%20people%20dead.%20A%20great%20deal%20of%20the%20focus%20was%20on%20Leopold%20II%20himself%20and%20his%20greed%2C%20which%20distracted%20attention%20away%20from%20the%20greater%20system%20of%20capitalist%20colonial%20expansion%20that%20was%20fully%20endorsed%20by%20Euro-American%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFamously%2C%20Leopold%20II%20never%20set%20foot%20in%20the%20Congo%20and%20neither%20did%20the%20art%20nouveau%20designers%20who%20fashioned%20buildings%20and%20exhibition%20pavilions%20relating%20to%20the%20Congo.%20I%20believe%20this%20distance%20from%20the%20realities%20of%20life%20in%20the%20Congo%20itself%20allowed%20for%20the%20fantastical%20forms%20that%20were%20created%20in%20Belgium.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20did%20you%20conclude%20about%20the%20Mobutu%20period%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMobutu%20Sese%20Seko%20was%20widely%20maligned%20by%20the%20Euro-American%20press.%20What%E2%80%99s%20often%20ignored%2C%20to%20this%20day%2C%20is%20that%20he%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theafricareport.com%2F58653%2Fdrc-how-the-cia-got-under-patrice-lumumbas-skin%2F%5C%22%3Eput%20in%20place%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20Belgium%20and%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20painted%20as%20the%20villain%20of%20the%20African%20story%2C%20fulfilling%20the%20ultimate%20caricature%20of%20the%20African%20kleptocrat%2C%20yet%20he%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20have%20come%20to%20power%20without%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20colonialism%20that%20came%20before%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBelgian%20colonialism%20followed%20a%20logic%20of%20extractivism%20(removing%20natural%20resources%20to%20export%20them)%20that%20forced%20the%20Congolese%20economy%20to%20supply%20raw%20materials%20to%20the%20west%20(especially%20Belgium)%2C%20which%20continues%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F05195511%2FPavillion-jpg.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22754%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F05195511%2FPavillion-jpg.jpg%20754w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F05195511%2FPavillion-jpg-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700281%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22503%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20wooden%20structure%20from%20the%201897%20Congo%20Pavilion.%20Photo%3A%20Ruth%20Sacks%2FThe%20Conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMobutu%20is%20considered%20corrupt%20in%20the%20Congo%20today%20and%20his%20military%20dictatorship%20was%20indeed%20brutal%20and%20controlled%20the%20Congolese%20people%20with%20fear.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20his%20commandeering%20of%20a%20cultural%20blooming%20in%20Kinshasa%20in%20the%20late%201960s%20and%20early%201970s%20was%20important.%20Instead%20of%20dismissing%20what%20he%20built%20as%20only%20the%20work%20of%20a%20dictator%2C%20my%20book%20draws%20out%20some%20of%20the%20complexity%20of%20this%20time%20and%20what%20it%20meant%20to%20celebrate%20African%20craft%2C%20art%20forms%20and%20traditional%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20of%20appropriating%20Euro-American%20artistic%20ideas%20and%20architectural%20styles%20in%20order%20to%20celebrate%20Africanness%2C%20as%20an%20anti-colonial%20statement%2C%20still%20holds%20weight%20today.%20Many%20of%20Mobutu%E2%80%99s%20towering%20monuments%20are%20considered%20objects%20of%20pride%20in%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20this%20live%20on%20today%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20something%20to%20be%20gained%20from%20looking%20at%20what%20is%20left%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20tragically%20violent%20regimes%20and%20how%20their%20structures%20are%20treated%20within%20both%20their%20societies%20and%20their%20immediate%20surroundings.%20How%20material%20culture%20is%20made%20is%20as%20important%20as%20what%20is%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReckoning%20with%20monuments%20and%20memorials%2C%20and%20considering%20how%20these%20are%20maintained%20in%20the%20city%2C%20can%20shed%20often%20unexpected%20insights%20into%20the%20ways%20histories%20are%20told.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F05195827%2FTower-of-exchange-jpg.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F05195827%2FTower-of-exchange-jpg.jpg%201000w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F05195827%2FTower-of-exchange-jpg-300x222.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700282%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22621%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ETower%20of%20Exchange%20in%20Limete%2C%20Kinshasa.%20Photo%3A%20Ruth%20Sacks%2FThe%20Conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20hope%20is%20that%20the%20book%20remains%20relevant%20as%20a%20sign%20there%20is%20value%20in%20picking%20apart%20material%20remains%20of%20regimes%20that%20aimed%20for%20total%20control%2C%20but%20never%20fully%20achieved%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20associations%20that%20build%20up%20around%20public%20spaces%20and%20exhibitions%20are%20not%20necessarily%20only%20to%20do%20with%20the%20circumstances%20of%20their%20making%2C%20but%20how%20these%20stories%20have%20been%20filtered%20over%20time.%20They%20can%20alienate%20people%20but%20they%20can%20also%20engender%20pride.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20extractivist%20attitudes%20I%20describe%20throughout%20the%20book%2C%20which%20see%20the%20Congo%20as%20a%20resource%20with%20bountiful%20raw%20natural%20materials%2C%20are%20still%20very%20much%20present%20in%20our%20day-to-day%20life.%20The%20cobalt%20in%20our%20smartphones%2C%20computers%20and%20electric%20cars%20is%20mined%20by%20labourers%20working%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.paradigmshift.com.pk%2Fcobalt-in-congo%2F%5C%22%3Enear%20slave%20conditions%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20feed%20our%20need%20for%20the%20latest%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Congo%20Style%20stays%20with%20historical%20examples%20in%20Kinshasa%2C%20the%20built%20material%20that%20follows%20colonial%20ecocide%20is%20the%20main%20topic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERuth%20Sacks%2C%20senior%20lecturer%20in%20visual%20art%2C%20University%20of%20Johannesburg.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0u%3Cem%3Ender%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fcongo-style-how-two-dictators-shaped-the-drcs-art-architecture-and-monuments-223393%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709652627000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F0